 Steps for universal harmony

 To commemorate the birthday of Jean-Georges Noverre (1727 - 1810), the creator of modern ballet, UNESCO has marked April 29 to be celebrated every year as International Dance Day. Besides celebrating the various forms of dance, the purpose of the occasion is to rejoice and revel in its universality, to overcome all political, cultural and ethnic barriers and bring people together in peace and friendship under its common language and rhetoric. Rajya Sangeet Academy, Eastern Zonal Cultural Centre, Indian Council for Cultural Relations, World Dance Alliance - Asia Pacific (West Bengal chapter) and West Bengal Dance Group Federation celebrate the occasion this year with a day-long concert. Morning session: Screening of documentaries on P. Govindan Kutty and Chandralekha; performances by Behala Ragini, Niharika Centre for Performing Arts, Charoibeti and Sapphire Creations Dance Workshop. Evening session: Performance by dancers from Cambodia (picture above); presentations by workshop Group I (Choreographer: Emma Powell of Australia) and by workshop Group II (Choreographer: I-Fen Tung of Taiwan); and performances by Darpani, Samskritiki Sreyaskar, Tarit Sarkar Ballet Troupe, Ranan, Kanakangi, Calcutta Dance Theatre, Hritaal and Ananda Shankar Centre for Performing Arts.

 lEvent: International Dance Day celebrations lWhen: Tomorrow; 10 am - 1 pm and 6 pm - 9 pm lWhere: Rabindra Sadan 

